90. qui minus ‘in what way less?' Sat. 11. 3, 311 qui ridi- culus minus illo? ib. 7, 96 qui peccas mium alque ego? Translate ‘And are our tuneful poets less troubled by this madness?' Qui minus is merely a rhetorical question, and does not at all mean qno modo fit ut minus? Bentley⁷s conjecture versat for vexat is needless; this absurd ‘mutual admiration' based upon vanity is not really, as he thinks, a matter of pleasure in the long run, rather than annoyance.
